box_description: Find My iPhone was an app and service provided by Apple Inc. that allowed remote location tracking of iOS devices, Mac computers, Apple Watch, and AirPods. It was replaced by the app Find My in iOS 13. The service itself was integrated into iOS and macOS, while enabled devices could be tracked using either an iOS app or the iCloud website.WikipediaMore at Wikipedia
